  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Petitions filed in Supreme Court to prevent Rajapaksas, officials from leaving Sri Lanka",
      "author": "Mahadiya Hamza",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka former national swimmer Julian Bolling, the local corruption watchdog Transparency International and two others filed a fundamental rights petition in the Supreme Court seeking a restraining order against former Prime Minister Mahinda Rajapaksa, his brother and former Finance Minister Basil Rajapaksa, former central bank governors W D Lakshman and Ajith Nivard Cabral and ex-Secretary to the Treasury S R Attygale.",
        "Former Minister of Finance Ali Sabry, Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe, incumbent central bank governor Nandalal Weerasinghe, the Monetary Board of the Central Bank, Mahinda Siriwardana Secretary to the Treasury/Minister of Finance, Saliya Peiris the President of the Bar Association and Isuru Balapatabendi Secretary of the Bar Association have been named as respondents.",
        "The petitioners state that following the July 09 uprising neither the petitioners nor the citizens are aware of the location from where the President nor the Prime Minister are carrying out their official duties as they have not appeared in public or even in the news.",
        "They say according to information they have received they believe the respondents may leave the country and thereby avoid giving information sought by the petitioners and prevent proper investigation.",
        "\u201cIn such circumstances, unless and until a proper and comprehensive investigation to the causes of the actions/non actions, the result of such actions/non actions are carried out, including a forensic audit of the reserves of the central bank (if necessary) and other relevant facts and data, neither the petitioners nor the citizens of the Sri Lanka nor the State itself would be in a position to ascertain such factors and take remedial actions so that no situation such as has taken place is repeated in the future,\u201d the petitioners state.",
        "In that regard, they state, the presence of the respondents Mahinda Rajapaksa, Basil Rajapaksa, Former Central Bank governor W D Lakshman, former Central Bank governor Ajith Nivard Cabral and S R Attygala former Secretary to the Treasury is vital for the proper and effectual determination of the matters brought before the judge.",
        "They want to restrain the above mentioned respondents from overseas travel without proper approval of the Supreme Court.",
        "\u201cThe petitioners state that unless the interim relief sought for in this Application are granted, grave and irreparable loss, harm, damage and prejudice to the fundamental rights of the petitioners and citizens of Sri Lanka would be caused and the instant application would be renderers nugatory.\u201d (Colombo/Jul12/2022)"
      ],
